caption: I take my family to this great spot quite often! This is my favorite restaurant to dine.  I go to this spot regularly. The food is excellent, the workers are courteous and the payment is decent. I like going in this spot to have a good meal.

This spot is worth a try. They serve big portions for fair prices. Regularly well organized and with great mood. Will come back again.
Excellent food

The best kitfo!  And staff were very attentive, wanting to ensure we were satisfied.
The best Ethiopian food in the area!

One of my favorite Ethiopian restaurants. I bring my family and friends here and we always have a great time. The culture is what we expect to get and they never fail on that. Good tastes like its made with love. I went to one in DC and the food came out I had to send it back and come here.
My first trip to an Ethiopian restaurant and it was fantastic! Chicken and vegetarian were our choices. Wonderful service too.
Nice service
loved it!
Great food, small but dynamic environment! Great service!
The best Ethiopian food in Silver Spring, and I've been to ALL of them. Get the vegetarian platter and fried fish combo plate and you won't be disappointed.
I constantly stop by grabbing some food in this place. I liked the efficient service and well prepared food. 5 stars from me.

I enjoyed the meal.
Great hospitality
Delicious and filling!

We were a bit indecisive- first choosing individual entrees, then deciding to split platters. Our waitress was very patient and gracious. She gave food and drink recommendations, and explained ingredients some of our party were unfamiliar with. The food was delicious and I can’t wait to go back!
I’m vegetarian and I absolutely love the veggie options. The food is perfectly spiced and the restaurant has a great ambiance. Staff are welcoming. Highly recommend this restaurant!

The food here at Addis Ababa Restaurant was very good, it came with a variety of different meats and sides. The food also comes with free unlimited orders of injera (spongy Ethiopian bread). The service was also very good, with friendly service. The parking was a bit of an issue but if your patient enough you’ll find something. Overall the food and atmosphere here is very good.
Very good Ethiopian joint that surpassed my expectations. Good taste, good price, and good service. Certainly recommend. Parking might be an issue though if you drive.
This is the Ethiopian version of cheers!
Mmmmm. The food is always sooo good. They allow dogs in the patio area. I always get the groupon deal.
The food is good. The service is a little slow even though they're very nice.
Wow. If you order a platter at most Ethiopian places you'll need a many item platter and some portion of it will be the good stuff. Here they just give you the good stuff. Expertly curated.
Best place to eat Ethiopian food

I have only been to a few Ethiopian places and this is by far the best one I’ve been to food wise.  I got a platter and some Ethiopian beer and it was insanely good.  If/when I come back to this part of the world I will definitely come here.  Definitely two thumbs up.
Low key, comfortable atmosphere, good authentic Ethiopian.

Food is so good. And the prices are just right for the quality and quantity. The spices are not overwhelming and compliment the beef so well (welp that just sounded pretentious). I love coming here, especially since the people are so nice.

Great Ethiopian food, at reasonable prices. This place is one of the first Ethiopian restaurants in Silver Spring, and continues to serve high quality dishes. Coupons are frequently available in Value Pak. Highly recommended.
Great food
The worst customer service I experienced in that area ..unprofessional manager..... very rude
Good
We went there for the groupon coupon they had, and the store was closed. It was open according Google maps.

Great food, great service. If you are looking for a different, palet stimulating, and all around awesome time then this is for you. As a person who enjoys different cuisines I rather enjoyed the experience. I will say that eating with my hands was a little strange to me but the food made up for it. Seeing all of the different ethnic groups eating and enjoying the food really shows you just how amazing and cultural this place is. Overall I give this place an 8.5 out of 10.
Very good Ethiopian food for the price
Great food. Service is very good, but a hit slow. Great vegetarian selection.
I think this may very well be the best in the DC area. Yeah, I know exactly how strong a statement that is.

Really nice service. Reasonable price and decent food. It’s a nice place to try Ethiopian food. I don’t think the Ethiopian honey wine is super good, so I would recommend to buy a glass if you just want to try it.
Amazing Ethiopian food at a good price!
Delicious, tasty, spicy, fresh and fun!
Great tests in a beautiful restaurant. Not my first time eating this type of food, and this one was very good. If you never tried it before, you should.
Love this place. The food is good and taste authentic. Cool environment and great price. Wait staff is friendly and polite.

This is the best Ethiopian restaurant I've been to in silver spring. The food is exploding in flavor, they help you figure out your order, portions, etc. They worked with us to get the kids meals setup on the table, the atmosphere is warm and comforting, and the staff are very friendly and welcoming. I'll always be back and drive an hour to get there whenever I need my Ethiopian fix now
Good food and customer service.
Very good food and friendly service!

My husband and I have been coming here for years. The food has always been delicious, and we've (almost) always received kind service. We had one bad interaction during a take-out order, but that was from someone we saw only that one time, so I wonder if it was a temporary staff member or if they got fired. Otherwise we tend to have the same servers for the most part, and they're always very friendly.  We went here very often before becoming vegetarians, but even now we feel like there are many delicious, flavorful options for us to choose from. They're great about seeing we're low on injera and bringing us more, which we appreciate! They do tend to let you sit and socialize a while, so if you're looking to leave faster, just flag down the waiter and them know you need the check. It's a fairly small place so they'll never really be out of site.

The food is simply "Delicious" .I tried their combination platter #3 which comes with kitfo, lega tibs, and doro wat. It was very "Delicious". Their service was fast and the food was mouthwatering.  I have tried  many Ethiopian restaurants in DC area, and Addis Ababa restaurant is one of my favorite. I enjoy every bite of food when I eat at Addis Ababa restaurant.
If u need nice food visit this place
Authentic Ethiopian cuisine coupled with great ambiance and excellent service. This place gets high marks across the board.
Nice place friendly atmosphere
Great food cool atmosphere

The food here used to be something really special, I'm not sure if it's under new management or they lost a chef, but it's gotten pretty lackluster. That being said, the service is always sweet and attentive and the decor is classic Ethiopian kitsch with carved wooden chairs and basket tables. I typically order the fish combo, which is a whole fried fish served alongside a selection of the vegetarian dishes (including yellow split peas, cabbage, and green beans). The sambusa appetizer is also tasty.

We happened to find this place while driving and looking for an Ethiopian restaurant and this is situated in am area where the are at least three more such restsurants... This place was full of people who were happily having beer and chatting, and everyone seemed to know everyone. We began to wonder if we should have gone elsewhere, as no one was eating, but once the food arrived, it put all doubts to rest. Everyone was there because they are friendly, have a great ambience, good service and serve excellent food! They helped us decide how much to order, so we do not over order and service was very prompt. The place was also clean and hygienic. Highly recommended..
Never had better eithiopian food in my life. Can't describe how good it is.

Its good restaurant. I go there at least once a month. Last time I went, I was with a friend who was visiting from Africa. But since she doesn't eat Injera, we decided to bring her food, but the manager would not let her eat inside the restaurant and almost kicked us out. I am probably never going back.
Yum

The manager was disrespectful. He will hurt the business. I am never going back.

Very tasty with excellent combo platters
Good food. Tried the vegetarian platter.it has a good variety of stuff for non meat eaters.
OMG! Best Ethiopian food EVER!

It's an ok place to go to, once in a while. The interior is dark. Their food is fresh, and quite spicy. It was my first time trying Ethiopian cuisine, we ordered a big platter that had bread at the bottom and different curries placed on top. You are supposed to eat with your hands. It's quite an adventure!!
Fantastic vegetarian options. Good service.
Very good food and good Ethiopian beer as well they have  daily happy hour very homey
Food is delicious and portions are big. My favorite Ethiopian near me.
First time trying Ethiopian food. It was delicious, I will definitely be going back there.

Soooooooo good

Good place to experience Ethiopian cuisine. Neat and well maintained
Great food. Generous portions. Ample selection. Cool atmosphere. Friendly and courteous service. Solid choice for date night or an evening out with the crew.
Great Ethiopian food in a friendly atmosphere.
Food was very good and came out super fast
One of my fav Ethiopian spots. Small and cozy. The food is great, wine and beer good, staff friendly, and the music right on.
A historical Ethiopian restaurant in silver spring
Food was really good. Not too expensive. Clean and spacious bathroom.
Still the best Ethiopian in downtown Silver Spring

Good food and service.
All food and drink prices are affordable.
One of the best Ethiopian Restaurants I've been to. The food was absolutely delicious. I would definitely recommend this place.

Excellent restaurant for a traditional Ethiopian meal. The ambiance is a bit classy but still casual. There is a bar but this is not the place you would come just for drinks. The prices are great value. The clientele seems always replete with actual Ethiopians.
The food taste great. The service was okay. Took awhile to get our food though.

solid and consistent restaurant.

Food was good and the people were very friendly. Small and cozy place. Feels like a family restaurant.
This is the place where you can get pleasure with your beloved.
Great local spot, and excellent service. I will be back!
My first time here and it was delicious.
Tasty food, cozy, friendly service and feel like Ethiopia
First time trying Ethiopian cuisine, and enjoyed it very much. Interesting decor too!
One spot I love in silver spring very home-y feeling... Love the ambiance great service and delicious food!!
Very good kitfo, a/c on high for a cool fall day. Asked waitress to change the TV channel-request denied. Family friendly. Not great tibs.
I've never had a dish I didn't love.
First time eating Ethiopian food and we had a great experience here. Everything we ate was delicious and the service was very helpful when ordering.
Delicious, great service, not touristy.
It was OK.

I have been to this restaurant many times before and absolutely love it. Nice waitresses!!. Delicious foods. Nothing I could really complain about except maybe the prices!! but its all the same really which ever Ethiopian restaurant you go to.

This is by far the worst restaurant service and food I have experianced. Our reservation was given to other coustumer when we showed up. Then the waitress was rude and disrespectful. Spilled water on one of my friend and didn't bother to help us clean up or provide napkins.  Took our order and then half way  tells us that they run out of food (injera) and wants to charge extra$$. Food was terrible and was not freshly made. I would not recommend this place for anyone that is trying to experience Ethiopian food and culture.

I ordered a Dora Fitfit which is supposed to be poultry and was given ONE piece of chicken.. ONE..the leg portion.. the rest was injera and one hard boiled egg.. I refuse to pay $16+ for one piece chicken
My favorite Ethiopian restaurant and the owner and staff are super kind to their customers. The must have dish -- vegetarian combo. Give it a try!
I love this place! Everytime I go the food tastes great. You may or may not get an attentive server, but the flavors never disappoint.

Not my favorite Ethiopian restaurant in the Spring, but it's still very good. The food choices and preparation feel a bit more friendly to Ethiopian customers, which is fine. The prices are reasonable, but the staff can often seem aloof.  There's almost always a Groupon, and with one it's very much worth your time. Without, check out Lagano around the block on Georgia for great food and service.
Delicious! We love Ethiopian food and finally found a place to where we can return when in DC area. Service extremely friendly and food authentic and tasty.
The ambiance was awesome and the service was good too. The food is simply awesome. Recommended!
Great Ethiopian Food. Service could be more prompt, but they are very nice otherwise.

I lived in Ethiopia for about 2 years, and I can testify that this is the only authentic Ethiopian food in DC.  The spices are authentic, last time we went they gave us ingenra with teff, not wheat.  They have harrar and other ethiopian beers.  Sure the service isn't great (but thats how you know your getting the real deal) and its not a good place to go if your a stuck-up DCites.  Most of the U st restaurants are marginal by comparison.  We have tried most of them, they are over-priced and under-spiced.  Overall its like being back in a high-end Ethiopian joint and all that comes with it (sans the digestive troubles)
